A warm welcome to the tiniest penguin on Earth.

The world's smallest penguin species has welcomed a delightful new arrival: Henry, a fairy penguin chick who hatched at SEA LIFE Weymouth in Dorset, UK.

Also known as little blue penguins for their striking blue-grey feathers that shimmer in the water, fairy penguins are the smallest of all penguin kinds. Adults typically stand just 30–40 cm tall—roughly the height of a standard loaf of bread—compared to the much taller emperor penguins.
